<TITLE> Younis to decide whether to go to court or appeal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 12 (bdnews24.com) -- Former captain Younis Khan will decide in a couple of days whether to file a case in a court against Pakistan Cricket Board or appeal against its decision to ban him for an indefinite period, reports PTI. Younis had earlier sent a notice to the PCB asking it to give reasons for the ban but the board directed him to file a formal appeal. Younis had met his lawyer Ahmed Qayyum and they would decide in a day or two whether to file a petition in court or lodge an appeal against the ban with the PCB. "Younis has signed all concerned documents and his case is very strong but we have to look at the issue from many aspects. That is why we are taking our time to decide on whether to go to court or file an appeal with the board," Qayyum 
